    <remarks variants="11">
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Foreign Service Officer. Inspector General of the Department of State and the Foreign Service; Director of the Bureau of Counterterrorism; Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Uruguay); Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Panama); Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary (Brazil).</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/people/sayre-robert-marion</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="2">
            <p>Office of Regional American Affairs, Department of State, until June 18, 1956; Acting Officer in Charge, Inter-American Security and Military Assistant Affairs, June 18, 1956-July 28, 1957; thereafter, Second Secretary, Embassy in Peru</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1955-57v06/persons#p_SRM1</source-url>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1955-57v07/persons#p_SRM1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Executive Secretary of the Task Force on Latin America, officer in charge Mexican Affairs, Office of Caribbean and Mexican Affairs, Bureau of Inter-American Affairs, September 1961-April 1962; thereafter Special Assistant to the President</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1961-63v12/persons#p_SRM4</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Director, Office of Mexican Affairs, Bureau of Inter-American Affairs, Department of State, until April 1964; member of the National Security Council staff until April 1965; Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for Inter-American Affairs April 1965–July 1968; Ambassador to Uruguay from July 24, 1968</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1964-68v31/persons#p_SRM1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>senior member, National Security Council staff, April 1964–April 1965; Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for Inter-American Affairs from April 1965; Acting Assistant Secretary of State for Inter-American Affairs, July 1, 1967–December 31, 1968</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1964-68v32/persons#p_SRM1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Ambassador to Panama</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76v05/persons#p_SRM1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Ambassador to Panama from October 31, 1969, until March 14, 1974; Inspector General of the Department of State and the Foreign Service from November 25, 1975, until May 1, 1978</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1969-76v22/persons#p_SRM_1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Ambassador to Panama until March 14, 1974; Inspector General of the Department of State and Foreign Service, November 25, 1975–May 1, 1978</p>
